{"ts":"2026-06-03T17:00:00Z","agent":"rust-implementer","decision":"RFC-0107 Phase B+C+D+E landed on feature/rfc-0107-subscribe (commits 303b89b, c911f59, 5f2f9c0). New mycelium-mcp/src/subscription.rs (873 lines) mirrors push.rs style with all frozen-at-v1 constants (METHOD=mycelium/subscriptionDelta, DEFAULT_TTL=3600s, MAX_SUBSCRIPTIONS=256, MAX_PER_CLIENT=32, MAX_SELECTOR=64, MAX_PER_ARRAY=50, MAX_FILES_PER_DELTA=16, MAX_SELECTOR_SOURCE_LEN=4096, ID_REGEX=^[A-Za-z0-9_-]{1,64}$). Interest tagged union (D1=d) + SubscriptionDeltaEvent/PerFileDelta wire shape (RFC-0107 §4) + (ii-strict) Selector removal semantics (D2). subscribe/unsubscribe/status/evict_expired/evict_for_dead_peer/bump_ttl/match_batch all implemented. UUID-v4 simple-form default ids. start_watch on_batch closure now fans out per-subscription notifications via tokio::spawn (rolling TTL bumped on each delivery; Selector last_match_set persisted post-send). 60s periodic eviction task spawned in serve_stdio. 3 new MCP tools (mycelium_subscribe/_unsubscribe/_subscription_status) registered — EXPECTED_TOOL_COUNT bumped 90→93. CLI `mycelium watch --subscribe '<SPEC>'` (Phase D-extra) prints NDJSON via the same subscription::match_batch code path, asserted byte-identical by tests/contract_subscription. 10 RFC-0107 §6 tests passing (3 in core: symbols_in_file + batch_delta_classifies + on_batch_signature_carries; 6 in mcp subscription::tests; 1 contract_subscription roundtrip) plus 6 extras (id_collision/invalid_interest/selector_too_large/files_empty-suppress/payload-shape-frozen/selector-evaluates). `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings` clean; `cargo test --workspace` green (all 30+ test suites pass, 0 failures). CHANGELOG Unreleased/Added bullet shipped; skills/index-management/SKILL.md gained the 3 tools + a §`mycelium/subscriptionDelta` section. RFC-0107 §10 acceptance checked off [x] all six rows. NOT pushed and NOT PR'd per founder rule — founder will open the PR.","rationale":"Single